<article id="post-1478" class="post-1478 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-general category-technology tag-domains tag-hosting tag-how-to tag-internet tag-websites">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2009/08/how-to-host-your-own-website-the-simple-version/" rel="bookmark">How to host your own website (the simple version)</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>I&#8217;ve been around this internet thing for a long time, and I&#8217;ve set up probably far more than my share of websites (both for myself and my clients). After a while, setting up websites becomes largely a by-rote-memory thing and you don&#8217;t have to put a lot of effort into it.<br />
But that belittles the reality: it&#8217;s not really that easy to set up a website if you have no idea how it&#8217;s done. And let&#8217;s be honest, here, I&#8217;m not talking about MySpace. I&#8217;m talking about using your own domain name (e.g. mytotallyawesomewebsite.com)   as a way of branding yourself, your message, and hopefully standing out from the crowd.<br />
One thing I can assure you, though: it&#8217;s also not that hard. Really.<br />
 <a href="http://geoff.wp/2009/08/how-to-host-your-own-website-the-simple-version/#more-1478" class="more-link">Continue reading<span class="screen-reader-text"> &#8220;How to host your own website (the simple version)&#8221;</span></a></p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	<footer class="entry-footer">
		<span class="byline"><span class="author vcard"><img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/095609f98b14811f33ecac14add504b3?s=49&#038;d=mm&#038;r=r' srcset='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/095609f98b14811f33ecac14add504b3?s=98&#038;d=mm&#038;r=r 2x' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49' loading='lazy'/><span class="screen-reader-text">Author </span> <a class="url fn n" href="http://geoff.wp/author/sonworf/">Geoff</a></span></span><span class="posted-on"><span class="screen-reader-text">Posted on </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/2009/08/how-to-host-your-own-website-the-simple-version/" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date published updated" datetime="2009-08-10T20:13:30-06:00">10 August 2009</time></a></span><span class="cat-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Categories </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/category/general/" rel="category tag">General</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/category/technology/" rel="category tag">Technology</a></span><span class="tags-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Tags </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/domains/" rel="tag">domains</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/hosting/" rel="tag">hosting</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/how-to/" rel="tag">how to</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/internet/" rel="tag">internet</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/websites/" rel="tag">websites</a></span><span class="comments-link"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2009/08/how-to-host-your-own-website-the-simple-version/#comments">3 Comments<span class="screen-reader-text"> on How to host your own website (the simple version)</span></a></span>			</footer><!-- .entry-footer -->
