		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2008/09/i-heart-google-chrome/" rel="bookmark">I (heart) Google Chrome</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>Not 45 minutes ago, Google released their latest contribution to the internet: <a href="http://www.google.com/chrome">Chrome</a>. This effectively ended years of speculation that Google was writing a browser, that it would throw its hat into the ring and kick off another heated browser war.  <br />
Figures that Google wouldn&#8217;t just drop a bomb, it would lay waste to the expectations of a browser. My hat is off to the <a href="http://www.google.com/googlebooks/chrome/">Chrome development team</a> &#8212; you guys pulled off a doozy.  <br />
